        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A group of rare autosomal recessive forms of ichthyosis clinically characterized by superficial asymptomatic spontaneous peeling of the skin and histologically by a shedding of the outer layers of the epidermis. PSS presents with either an acral (acral PSS) or a generalized distribution for generalized PSS type A (noninflammatory) or B (inflammatory)."
        },
